  ideas to visualise and test them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.255882Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-27153-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Modelling helps to understand scale, proportion, and form in 3D."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.255887Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-27151-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Standardised components can be mass produced which lowers cost."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.259459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-27151-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Standardised components allow manufacturers to specialise on the product rather than
  the individual parts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.259463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-27151-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Standardised components are components that are produced in a set size for a range
  of uses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.259466Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-27151-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Standardised components are more cost efficient due to the products being able to be
  mass produced."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.259470Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-27195-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Voltage, current and resistance are the key concepts when designing electronic
